James.
Yeah.

26:06.521 --> 26:09.263
James, do you think
you can find him?

26:12.788 --> 26:14.660
Well, thank you, James.
Thank you very much.

26:14.703 --> 26:17.663
That will mean a lot
to his mom.

26:17.706 --> 26:22.624
You want me
to find him, Pa?

26:22.668 --> 26:24.974
Yeah.

26:25.018 --> 26:33.156
♪♪

26:33.200 --> 26:34.810
No. No way.

26:34.854 --> 26:37.030
You're broke.

26:37.073 --> 26:41.164
Go on.

26:41.208 --> 26:43.950
For your expenses
in finding our son.

26:43.993 --> 26:49.042
We do all right,
our church.

26:49.085 --> 26:52.611
Okay.

26:52.654 --> 26:55.614
Uh, this is
all of it.

26:55.657 --> 26:59.269
Ma keeps it.

26:59.313 --> 27:03.926
Social security, birth
certificate -- Will that help?

27:03.970 --> 27:07.060
Yeah.

27:07.103 --> 27:09.671
We wanted to give you
something else.

27:09.715 --> 27:14.371
For your...graduation.

27:14.415 --> 27:17.461
It's a fresh start
for you.

27:17.505 --> 27:22.945
Fill it out.

27:22.989 --> 27:26.383
We make a little unit, see --
you, me, and Ma.

27:26.427 --> 27:28.734
You'll be
under our wing.

27:28.777 --> 27:30.953
We have some pull around town.
Don't get too excited.

27:30.997 --> 27:34.827
It won't get you a car
or anything, but with this,

27:34.870 --> 27:37.917
you can get a checking account,
new cellphone,

27:37.960 --> 27:41.616
small line of credit.

27:41.660 --> 27:44.184
Not much.

27:44.227 --> 27:46.752
A start.

27:46.795 --> 27:55.848
♪♪

27:55.891 --> 27:58.154
Hey.

27:58.198 --> 28:00.591
You deserve it.

28:00.635 --> 28:03.377
Congratulations.

28:03.420 --> 28:06.467
♪♪

28:06.510 --> 28:08.861
[ Door opens, closes ]

28:08.904 --> 28:18.740
♪♪

28:18.784 --> 28:28.663
♪♪

28:28.707 --> 28:30.491
[ Metal creaks ]

28:30.534 --> 28:33.015
[ Speaking Spanish ]

28:50.598 --> 28:52.165
Mexico?

28:52.208 --> 28:54.036
What's Paul doing
in Mexico, James?

28:54.080 --> 28:57.953
He's sick, Pa.
It's grave.

28:57.997 --> 29:00.173
Ma, I'm sorry.
He's very sick.

29:00.216 --> 29:02.566
Why isn't he here?
Why is he there?

29:02.610 --> 29:05.352
He's in a prison.
He's in a prison hospital.

29:05.395 --> 29:08.747
In Hermosillo.Good Lord.

29:08.790 --> 29:11.880
Pa.

29:11.924 --> 29:15.101
Is he...what?
Sick, how?

29:15.144 --> 29:19.801
I didn't gather.
Liver failure.

29:19.845 --> 29:25.111
They said, uh, hepatitis.
Something concerning that.

29:25.154 --> 29:27.548
They said late stages.
That was clear.

29:27.591 --> 29:31.291
Son.

29:31.334 --> 29:34.685
Oh, James.

29:34.729 --> 29:39.429
There's
a sheriff there.

29:39.473 --> 29:41.823
It's a little different
than here.

29:41.867 --> 29:44.565
There's a sheriff there

29:44.608 --> 29:47.350
who oversees the prison
and the county.

29:47.394 --> 29:50.614
It's different.

29:50.658 --> 29:53.617
We spoke privately.

29:53.661 --> 29:55.402
He'll let him go.

29:55.445 --> 29:57.230
You have to go there.

29:57.273 --> 30:01.016
You have to pay him,
but they'll let him go.

30:01.060 --> 30:10.504
♪♪

30:10.547 --> 30:19.992
♪♪

30:20.035 --> 30:29.479
♪♪

30:29.523 --> 30:32.656
[ Keys ticking ]

30:32.700 --> 30:36.182
[ Line ringing ]

30:36.225 --> 30:39.315
What do you mean "wait"?
They're on their way.

30:39.359 --> 30:42.884
Man: I might not want
to do it anymore.

30:42.928 --> 30:46.801
What the fuck
you talking -- What?

30:46.845 --> 30:50.761
Yeah, I might change my mind.
I'm still deciding.

30:50.805 --> 30:53.373
They're on
their way, man.

30:53.416 --> 30:55.201
What are you still --
What do you --

30:55.244 --> 30:57.290
What do you mean you're
still deciding? Decide.

30:57.333 --> 31:00.946
[ Sighs ] You have --
You have 10 minutes, okay?

31:00.989 --> 31:05.864
Wow, man.

31:05.907 --> 31:10.346
Not cool.

31:10.390 --> 31:13.045
[ Cellphone beeps ]

