40:38.392 --> 40:41.134
Woman: Paul Brown,
your fax is ready.

40:41.177 --> 40:44.572
♪♪

40:44.616 --> 40:46.487
Paul Brown?

40:46.531 --> 40:56.454
♪♪

40:56.497 --> 41:06.420
♪♪

41:06.464 --> 41:08.770
Glenn:
Can I help you?

41:08.814 --> 41:13.688
I don't --
I don't see you, man.

41:13.732 --> 41:17.649
Over here, at the counter,
ready to assist you.

41:26.440 --> 41:30.270
I have to stay off my feet
due to an event.

41:30.313 --> 41:32.533
Hm.

41:32.577 --> 41:36.319
Anything you'd like
to buy or sell?

41:36.363 --> 41:40.019
Just browsing, okay?

41:40.062 --> 41:42.891
Okay.
Take your time.

41:42.935 --> 41:44.545
Let me know if you have
any questions.

41:44.589 --> 41:46.939
My name's Glenn.

41:51.596 --> 41:53.293
You hurt
your head, Glenn?

41:53.336 --> 41:55.208
Someone else did.

41:55.251 --> 41:56.775
Someone ruthless.

41:56.818 --> 42:00.169
He bludgeoned me.

42:00.213 --> 42:03.216
Bludgeoned?

42:03.259 --> 42:05.958
Yeah.

42:06.001 --> 42:08.656
Do you know
what that word means?

42:08.700 --> 42:12.486
No. I just heard
Sheriff Dolittle say it.

42:12.530 --> 42:16.011
It means he hit you,
like, many times.

42:16.055 --> 42:19.798
He did.

42:19.841 --> 42:22.235
You're gonna count
those first two?

42:22.278 --> 42:26.108
'Cause maybe those weren't,
like, actual blows.

42:26.152 --> 42:31.679
And maybe that's not fair
to the guy to...count them.

42:31.723 --> 42:34.943
Yeah, I'm gonna
count them.

42:34.987 --> 42:37.555
Okay.

42:41.994 --> 42:45.171
You want a milkshake
or something?

42:45.214 --> 42:48.348
Why not.

42:48.391 --> 42:50.959
[ Door opens, bell jingles ]

43:14.287 --> 43:16.811
[ Door opens, bell jingles ]

43:16.855 --> 43:19.814
Arson's ruthless.

43:19.858 --> 43:21.294
Murder.

43:21.337 --> 43:22.991
Yeah.
Yeah.

43:23.035 --> 43:24.645
For sure.

43:24.689 --> 43:31.173
Robbery, mm, even with
a small assault, not really.

43:31.217 --> 43:34.437
My vocabulary,
I have to tell you --

43:34.481 --> 43:36.483
It's not
a source of pride.

43:36.526 --> 43:38.137
That's because you work
in a pawn shop.

43:38.180 --> 43:43.621
You should be
in 10th grade.

43:43.664 --> 43:45.971
Sorry that happened
to you, man.

43:46.014 --> 43:50.236
[ Sniffs ]Yeah.

43:50.279 --> 43:56.982
The guy probably had
a good reason.

43:57.025 --> 44:00.246
Maybe he'll come by later
and bring you, like...

44:00.289 --> 44:03.075
2,000 bucks
or something.

44:03.118 --> 44:05.381
Soon.

44:05.425 --> 44:06.948
Like a couple weeks.

44:06.992 --> 44:09.211
That would be
pretty fuckin' cool.

44:09.255 --> 44:11.039
Yeah.

44:11.083 --> 44:13.781
I wonder
what his reason was.

44:13.825 --> 44:15.348
Just took
five shitty necklaces.

44:15.391 --> 44:17.698
I'm sure it was
a really great reason, yeah.

44:17.742 --> 44:20.745
And you'd probably understand
if you knew.

44:20.788 --> 44:23.661
[ Slurps ]

44:23.704 --> 44:26.098
Hey.

44:26.141 --> 44:31.233
Thanks for the new vocab...
and the shake.

44:31.277 --> 44:33.322
But we're clear
on that,

44:33.366 --> 44:36.238
that the guy who gave you
a little tap?

44:36.282 --> 44:38.676
He's not ruthless.

44:38.719 --> 44:41.113
It wasn't just
a little tap, man.

44:41.156 --> 44:44.638
I'm wearing a helmet here.

44:44.682 --> 44:47.380
You gonna
be all right?

44:47.423 --> 44:50.296
Long-term?
Did they say, Glenn?

44:50.339 --> 44:52.907
Just have to stay
off my feet.

44:52.951 --> 44:54.430
Should be all right.

44:54.474 --> 44:56.737
Hey, I'm Paul.

44:56.781 --> 44:59.392
Paul Allen Brown.

44:59.435 --> 45:02.787
I'm Glenn Pirdoo.
Nice to meet you, Paul.

45:02.830 --> 45:04.963
What brings you
to Half Acre?

45:05.006 --> 45:06.616
Parents.
Cool.

45:06.660 --> 45:08.706
Yeah, they just died,
though, so...

45:08.749 --> 45:10.490
That's...not cool.

45:10.533 --> 45:11.926
No.

45:11.970 --> 45:13.362
S-Sorry about that.

45:13.406 --> 45:18.672
Yeah.

45:18.716 --> 45:20.935
All right. See you.

45:20.979 --> 45:23.721
See you, man.

45:27.333 --> 45:29.291
[ Slurps ]

45:29.335 --> 45:31.859
[ Indistinct conversations ]

45:43.305 --> 45:46.134
[ Door bangs open ]

45:50.704 --> 45:53.489
[ Door bangs shut ]

46:03.848 --> 46:06.807
Hey, lady.

46:06.851 --> 46:09.549
I like your shoes.

46:09.592 --> 46:12.987
Hey, lady.

46:13.031 --> 46:16.599
I like your shoes.

46:16.643 --> 46:21.213
James: I used to get
bad feelings when I was a kid.

46:21.256 --> 46:25.870
Just like everyone else --
normal bad feelings.

46:25.913 --> 46:29.177
When I did,
I would call my dad.

46:29.221 --> 46:31.310
[ Cellphone beeping ]

46:31.353 --> 46:35.836
10 years ago,
I couldn't anymore.

46:35.880 --> 46:38.534
But I still do.

46:38.578 --> 46:40.841
[ Cellphone ringing ]

46:40.885 --> 46:43.626
♪♪

46:43.670 --> 46:46.804
[ Cellphone beeps ]

46:46.847 --> 46:53.419
Dad. You got your helmet on,
right, Dad?

46:53.462 --> 46:58.163
'Cause I can't hear you.

46:58.206 --> 47:01.688
Yeah, I can't hear you, Dad,
through your helmet.

47:01.731 --> 47:07.041
♪♪

47:07.085 --> 47:12.046
Well, all right.

47:12.090 --> 47:15.049
Bye, Dad.

47:15.093 --> 47:17.269
[ Cellphone beeps ]

47:17.312 --> 47:25.886
♪♪

47:29.455 --> 47:38.943
[ Speaking Spanish ]

47:38.986 --> 47:42.424
I'm going to kill you,
motherfucker.

47:42.468 --> 47:45.775
I'm the pale horse of Death,
and Hell follows me, boy.

47:45.819 --> 47:47.777
I am bathed in the blood
of the lamb,

47:47.821 --> 47:51.390
you spic coward cocksucker.

47:51.433 --> 47:53.261
Prepare for the Devil.

47:53.305 --> 47:56.525
I shall deliver you
unto his fucking kingdom come.

47:56.569 --> 48:05.447
♪♪

48:05.491 --> 48:07.972
[ Cellphone ringing, vibrating ]

48:08.015 --> 48:13.716
♪♪

48:13.760 --> 48:19.418
♪♪

48:19.461 --> 48:21.811
[ Cellphone beeps ]

48:21.855 --> 48:22.812
Yeah?

48:22.856 --> 48:24.945
Man:
Check your e-mail.

48:24.989 --> 48:26.642
I told you not
to contact me there, man.

48:26.686 --> 48:28.514
I don't care.
Check your e-mail.

48:28.557 --> 48:31.647
He just killed a 24-year-old kid
with his shoe.

48:31.691 --> 48:40.352
♪♪

48:40.395 --> 48:49.013
♪♪

48:49.056 --> 48:57.760
♪♪

48:57.804 --> 49:06.421
♪♪

49:06.465 --> 49:09.033
[ Truck door opens, shuts ]

49:09.076 --> 49:18.172
♪♪

49:18.216 --> 49:20.870
Hello.

49:20.914 --> 49:24.222
Hello.

49:24.265 --> 49:27.442
What's up?

49:27.486 --> 49:30.358
Nothing much.

49:30.402 --> 49:32.752
This your home?

49:32.795 --> 49:35.059
Family home, yeah.

49:35.102 --> 49:38.323
What can I do for you?

49:38.366 --> 49:41.630
Paul Brown?
Yeah.

49:41.674 --> 49:48.333
I'm Texas Ranger Wesley Walker,
greater Austin.

49:48.376 --> 49:56.123
I've been looking for you, Paul,
for a long time, now.

49:56.167 --> 50:00.780
You just got a new
driver's license, yeah?

50:00.823 --> 50:02.825
Yeah.

50:02.869 --> 50:06.438
Okay.

50:06.481 --> 50:09.963
That's how I got here.

50:10.007 --> 50:13.749
That's how I found you here
at this address.

50:13.793 --> 50:17.971
Yeah, I said,
"How can I help you?"

50:18.015 --> 50:23.020
Yeah, I've been looking for you
for a while.

50:23.063 --> 50:25.848
Can we talk?

50:25.892 --> 50:29.200
What do you want
to talk about?

50:29.243 --> 50:33.900
About the little girl.

50:33.943 --> 50:37.860
About the dead little girl
at the river.

50:37.904 --> 50:40.385
You're a person
of interest.

50:40.428 --> 50:43.257
Maybe not generally,
but in regard to the murder

50:43.301 --> 50:47.087
of Theresa
Sincere Williams,

50:47.131 --> 50:52.397
you are a person of interest, so
I'm going to question you.

50:56.183 --> 50:59.969
Let's go talk
about this, Paul.

51:02.755 --> 51:07.107
Do you want to get started
with some questions?

51:07.151 --> 51:10.980
Okay.

51:11.024 --> 51:15.637
You're Paul Allen Brown,
you said.

51:15.681 --> 51:24.472
♪♪

51:24.516 --> 51:33.264
♪♪

51:33.307 --> 51:42.142
♪♪

51:42.186 --> 51:45.145
You're Paul Allen Brown,
you said.

51:45.189 --> 51:47.365
Yes.

51:47.408 --> 51:52.109
Son of Byron
and Lillian Brown.

51:52.152 --> 51:55.199
Yes.

51:55.242 --> 51:58.202
James:
He asked me back there if I was
Paul Brown, and I said yes.

51:58.245 --> 52:00.334
Now what?

52:00.378 --> 52:03.424
Can you imagine the hundreds
of thousands of details --

52:03.468 --> 52:04.947
middle school,
your favorite color,

52:04.991 --> 52:07.428
the name of your
little-league baseball team?

52:07.472 --> 52:10.170
Can you imagine the hundreds
of thousands of things

52:10.214 --> 52:11.650
that you wouldn't know

52:11.693 --> 52:13.130
if you were pretending to be
someone else?

52:13.173 --> 52:16.220
I covered all this with Paul --
all of it.

52:16.263 --> 52:17.786
But I didn't think to ask

52:17.830 --> 52:20.180
if he was a person of interest
in a murder.

52:20.224 --> 52:22.574
I figured
he would've told me that.

52:22.617 --> 52:24.445
What else didn't he tell me?

52:24.489 --> 52:26.795
What else?

52:26.839 --> 52:32.801
♪♪

